# Keep docs in sync with code changes

When you introduce, change, or remove a **feature, public API, option, default, event name, export path, or behavior** in this monorepo, treat documentation as part of the same change — not a follow-up.

## Required impact check

Before finishing the work, identify what is affected and update it:

1. **Package user docs** — `packages/<pkg>/docs/*.md` (source of truth; synced into VitePress)
2. **Adapter / sibling package docs** — `packages/<pkg>-*/README.md` and `docs/README.md` when the core contract changes
3. **Site guides** that are **not** synced from package docs — e.g. `apps/docs/docs/packages/<pkg>/guides|faq|tutorials|best-practices/**` — fix invented or stale examples
4. **Sidebars** — `apps/docs/docs/.vitepress/*-sidebar.ts` when adding/renaming/removing module pages
5. **Cross-links** — overview learning paths, “Related”, “Previous/Next”, entrypoint tables, playground deep links
6. **Playground** copy/examples only when they document the changed API

Engineering notes under `packages/<pkg>/engineering/` and `_construction/` are maintainer-only — do **not** treat them as user docs, but do update user docs when an ADR ships.

## What “complete docs” means

For each new or changed public surface:

- Document **options, defaults, and failure modes** (not only a happy-path snippet)
- Prefer **option tables** next to factories/config objects
- Call out **gotchas** (quirks, version selection, SSR, offline, naming mismatches)
- Keep examples matching **real types/exports** — never invent config shapes
- Fix or remove **stale** claims (“not yet”, wrong event names, wrong snapshot fields)
- After editing package docs, run `node scripts/sync-documentation.mjs` (or `pnpm` docs sync) when verifying the live site

IA and sync model: `packages/form-intelligence/engineering/010-documentation-standard.md`.

## Do not

- Ship a public API change with docs that only name-drop the feature
- Update TypeScript types/exports without the matching guide (or mark the gap explicitly if the user scoped docs out)
- Leave broken internal links or sidebar entries pointing at removed pages
- Duplicate the same how-to as both a Concept and a Guide

## Quick examples

| Code change | Docs to touch |
| ----------- | ------------- |
| New form option / plugin | Guide page + `entrypoints.md` / integrations if import path changes + related cross-links |
| Renamed event (`connectivity:*` → `connection:*`) | Module guide, overview, concepts, site FAQ/guides, playground copy |
| New package docs page | New `packages/<pkg>/docs/<page>.md` + sidebar entry + overview learning path |
| Adapter API change | Adapter `README.md` + `docs/README.md` + core `adapters.md` if it describes that adapter |
